<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-46-1101 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Science and Technology Agency made a survey, in Honjo City on variousregeneratable energies. During 1981 - 1984, an integrated utilizationequipment which combined geothermal, wind and solar heat was installedat a nursery home for the aged people. The result of operating this systemshowed that the room heating and hot water supply energies could be accommodated:19% by geothermal energy, 8% by wind energy and 25% by solar heat. (2figs, 1 tab)</TEXT></DOC>